  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">17</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Based on the demand on simple online information on rainwater harvesting, 3R and Environmental Sustainability in WASH, RAIN in collaboration, Rainbow Collection and Wetlands International developed several tools that support practitioners in water management planning.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CAP</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Environmental sustainability : These tools are directly focusing on providing information on Environmental Sustainability. They support practitioners from NGOs and governmental organisations to integrate aspects like rainwater harvesting, 3R and Environmental Sustainability in WASH in water management plans and projects.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">How to integrate rainwater harvesting in your project? How do integrate Environmental Sustainability in WASH projects? Where to find more detailed technical rainwater harvesting solutions? How to identify the potential of rainwater harvesting in your country or project area? Let these tools support you in this. Need advice? Contact us.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">I,E,T,S</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">INT</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting implementers and decision makers in uptake of RWH</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">These tools are directly focusing on providing information on Environmental Sustainability. They support practitioners from NGOs and governmental organisations to integrate aspects like rainwater harvesting, 3R and Environmental Sustainability in WASH in water management plans and projects.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">These tools will provide practitioners with easily accessible information on rainwater harvesting, 3R and Environmental Sustainability, by taking visitors through the information in a step by step approach, linking also to other online available information and tools.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This information will soon be available</narrative>
